  "Which of the following is an example of an endothermic process?": "",
  "Melting ice absorbs heat from the surroundings to break intermolecular bonds in the solid structure. That's why ice in a drink makes it cold — the ice absorbs thermal energy from the liquid. Burning, freezing, and condensation all release energy (exothermic).": ""
